inal disorders. Phenolic acids, including caffeic acid and ferulic acid, possess antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory effects, which may help prevent infections and reduce inflammation. Terpenoids, including carotenoids and xanthophylls, have been found to have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, which contribute to the plant's potential therapeutic benefits.", "properties": [], "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Silene atropurpurea are its anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial activities. The plant's ability to exhibit anti-inflammatory effects is attributed to its rich content of flavonoids and phenolic acids. Its antioxidant properties, which help protect cells from oxidative damage, are associated with the presence of saponins and volatile oils. Additionally, Silene atropurpurea's antimicrobial properties, useful in the treatment of infections, can be attributed to the presence of terpenoids and glycosides. These bioactive compounds contribute to the plant's ability to also exhibit hepatoprotective and cardioprotective effects.", "preparations": [{"name": "infusion", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 171, "total_score": 3420}, {"name": "tincture", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 156, "total_score": 3120}, {"name": "tea", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 141, "total_score": 2820}, {"name": "salve", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 108, "total_score": 2160}, {"name": "decoction", "mentions": 11, "confidence_score": 52, "total_score": 572}, {"name": "ointment", "mentions": 6, "confidence_score": 28, "total_score": 168}, {"name": "poultice", "mentions": 6, "confidence_score": 20, "total_score": 120}, {"name": "infused oil", "mentions": 3, "confidence_score": 11, "total_score": 33}, {"name": "smoking mix", "mentions": 1, "confidence_score": 3, "total_score": 3}], "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Silene atropurpurea are made from its leaves and flowers. Infusion is prepared by stee